- VSCode Version: 1.3.1
- OS Version: Ubuntu 15.10

Steps to Reproduce:

I have a webpack config with an alias for an import path, VSCode doesn't recognize this, i've tried with 
the `tsconfig.json`'s paths option:

``` json
{
  "compilerOptions": {
    "target": "es5",
    "module": "commonjs",
    "emitDecoratorMetadata": true,
    "experimentalDecorators": true
  },
  "filesGlob": [
    "**/*.ts",
    "!node_modules/**/*"
  ],
  "exclude": [
    "node_modules",
    "typings/global",
    "typings/global.d.ts"
  ],
  "paths": {
    "tao-animations": "app/theme/core/app.tao-animations.ts"
  },
  "compileOnSave": true,
  "atom": {
    "rewriteTsconfig": false
  }
}
```

But it still doesn't find the module even if webpack compiles ok:
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/9698639/16816733/f80f40b4-4904-11e6-91bf-cac6644f8d88.png)

vscode autocompletes the closing ), ] or } even when there is no need to (the need is determined by my subjective preferences to write code, not by syntax). This becomes especially inconvenient when I need to wrap an existing chunk of code:

``` js
function () { // <-- I've started typing this to wrap the three vars below
var a = 1;
var b = 2;
var c = 3;
```

At this point vscode inserts the closing } so I need to remove that } and insert it at the right place.

- VSCode Version: 1.3.1
- OS Version: OS X 10.11.3

**Steps to Reproduce:**
1. Open a CSS file that has a color declaration (e.g. `border: 1px solid red`) in it. A color preview should be visible.
2. Set your cursor to a (non-empty) line above or below the color declaration.
3. Move the line up or down by using the `alt` + `arrow-up/arrow-down` shortcut so that it switches the line with the line from step 1.

**Observations:**
- When moving a line from the bottom _above_ the line with the color preview, the preview square sticks to the left of the moving line.
-  When moving a line from the top _below_ the line with the color preview, the preview square becomes invisible.
- In both cases, the preview resets itself to its original location after a short time.
- The issue persists when starting VSC with `--disable-extensions`.

**Test code snippet:**

``` css
.test {
  display: block;
  border: 1px solid red;
  width: 100px;
  height: 100px;
  background-color: green;
  position: relative;
}
```

